<!-- ===================== BEAMERS STANDARD ===================== -->
<section class="standards-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
      <h2 class="section-headline">The Beamers Standard</h2>
      <p class="section-sub mx-auto">
        These aren't rules. They're the reason Beamers exists.
        Before you apply, make sure this resonates.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="standards-list">

      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="standard-item-header">
          <span class="standard-numeral">I</span>
          <h3 class="standard-heading">The Spell, Not the Wand</h3>
        </div>
        <p>AI has given everyone a magic wand. But a wand without spells is just a stick.
        Beamers are the people who put in years learning the spells: the expertise, the
        intuition, the muscle memory that turns a prompt into a result. This isn't traditional
        tech support, and it isn't a dev agency. It's what AI has made possible:
        <strong>fast, precise, genuinely useful help delivered through deep knowledge of modern
        tools.</strong> Everyone has the wand. Beamers know the spells.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="standard-item-header">
          <span class="standard-numeral">II</span>
          <h3 class="standard-heading">Tech Through Education</h3>
        </div>
        <p>The only real difference between a tech person and a non-tech person is the time
        they've spent with the tools. Beamers grant wishes. But a retainer means something
        more: <strong>the client is willing to learn, and you're willing to teach.</strong>
        Not just "here's the answer" but "here's how this works." People who think they
        "just don't get computers" haven't had someone take the time to show them. The goal
        is a client who understands their tools better after every session, not one who is
        more dependent on you.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="standard-item-header">
          <span class="standard-numeral">III</span>
          <h3 class="standard-heading">Open Tools, Open Paths</h3>
        </div>
        <p>Signing up is easy. Leaving is the trap. Beamers steer clients toward open,
        interoperable tools: ones with <strong>MCP servers, public repositories, and a
        genuine commitment to the new era.</strong> If a tool's business model depends on
        lock-in, or if the company's answer to AI is "AI bad," we find another tool.
        We have a duty to teach the value of open source and tool independence so clients
        are never held hostage by a price hike or a platform decision made without them.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="standards-cta text-center">
      <p class="standards-cta-label">Does this resonate?</p>
      <a href="/eoi/" class="btn-gold">Submit an Expression of Interest</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


